y and Enlightenment ideology, and analysing each theme in terms of its broad contemporary historical significance. This book will appeal to students and academics with an interest in the period, or politics, religion or science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aScientistszIrelandvBiography. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  a1798 rebellion.  aAgricultural improvement.  aBasalt.  aBotany.  aIrish Union.  aNapoleonic Wars.  aProvincial science.1 aBlackstock, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526111814423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526111814/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013